org.spongepowered.api.entity.living

Interface Ageable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Agent, DataHolder, Entity, EntityState, Identifiable, Living
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Animal, Chicken, Cow, Horse, Mooshroom, Ocelot, Pig, Rabbit, Sheep, Squid, Villager, Wolf, Zombie, ZombiePigman

    public interface Ageable
extends Agent
    Represents a living entity that can change in size as it ages and can spawn children.

    • Method Detail

      • getAge

        int getAge()
        Gets the age of this entity.
        Returns:
        The current age of this entity

      • setAge

        void setAge(int age)
        Sets the age of this entity.

        Negative ages tend to equate to the entity being a baby and therefor can not breed more of this entity. Setting a positive age tends to equate to the entity being an adult and able to breed children.

        Parameters:
        age - The age of this entity

      • setBaby

        void setBaby()
        Sets the age of this entity to the minimum required to be considered a baby. Babies tend to be unable to breed.

      • setAdult

        void setAdult()
        Sets the age of this entity to the minimum required to be considered a full grown adult and able to breed.

      • isBaby

        boolean isBaby()
        Returns true if this entity is considered an adult.
        Returns:
        True if this entity is an adult

      • canBreed

        boolean canBreed()
        Returns true if this entity is able to breed. Some entities have cooldowns between being able to breed new entities.
        Returns:
        True if this entity is able to breed

      • setBreeding

        void setBreeding(boolean breeding)
        Sets whether this entity can breed a new child.
        Parameters:
        breeding - Whether this entity can breed

      • setScaleForAge

        void setScaleForAge()
        Sets the scaling to be 1 if this entity is an adult and 0.5 if it is a baby.
